# Claude Code (~/.claude) — track config only, ignore runtime + secrets.
# Whitelist approach: ignore everything, then re-include the config we manage.
claude/*
!claude/settings.json
!claude/keybindings.json
!claude/CLAUDE.md
!claude/hooks/
!claude/commands/
!claude/agents/
!claude/skills/
# plugins/ holds only machine-specific runtime state (cache, clones, install paths).
# Reproducibility comes from settings.json: extraKnownMarketplaces + enabledPlugins
# auto-install everything on startup. So plugins/ stays fully ignored.

# IntelliJ — track config only, ignore machine-local state.
# Unlike claude/ and pi/, the whole IntelliJ config dir CANNOT be symlinked
# (version-specific path, machine state mixed with config). Settings Sync
# handles cross-machine sync for keymaps/codestyles/options. The dotfiles
# repo tracks only .ideavimrc (symlinked to ~/.ideavimrc) and reference
# copies of keymaps for version history.
intellij/*
!intellij/ideavimrc
!intellij/keymaps/
!intellij/MIGRATION-ADVISORY.md
/pi/pi-acp/session-map.json
